The paper deals with the problem of text passage alignment across interlingual article pairs in Wikipedia, which involves natural language processing, information retrieval, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses semantic similarity measures and greedy algorithms, which are common in information retrieval and artificial intelligence, respectively, suggesting cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DL (Machine Learning) as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves user studies and benchmarking, which are relevant to human-computer interaction and evaluation, indicating cs.LG (Learning) as a possible sub-category.
